# Agent Offboarding Rule

When offboarding an agent session, you MUST follow this checklist:

## Pre-Offboarding Checklist

- TODO

- [ ] All file changes committed to Git with descriptive commit message
- [ ] Session Note created in `docs/agents/session-notes/`
- [ ] Decision Docket updated with key decisions made
- [ ] TODO Log updated with current state and carryover items
- [ ] Any pending work items documented for next session

## Offboarding Actions

- TODO

- [ ] Revoke any temporary access tokens (if applicable)
- [ ] Clear any ephemeral caches or temporary files
- [ ] Archive session outputs in appropriate directories
- [ ] Update any ADRs with new rules or risks discovered

## Required Files to Update

1. **Session Note**: Use template from `docs/agents/templates/Session_Note_Template.md`
2. **Decision Docket**: Update `docs/global/Decision_Docket.md`
3. **TODO Log**: Update `docs/global/TODO_Log.md`
4. **Git Commit**: Include all changes with descriptive message

## Session Note Naming Convention

- Format: `SN_YYYYMMDD_<TaskId>.md`
- Example: `SN_20250927_PRD-Best-Practices-Definition.md`

## Commit Message Format

- Format: `feat: [brief description] - Session: [TaskId]`
- Example: `feat: Define PRD best practices and templates - Session: PRD-Best-Practices-Definition`

